<a href="javascript:card_browser(98)">Unfamiliar Territory</a> x 4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(82)">Host of Thousands</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(75)">Goblin Scimitar</a> x 4<br>
Such A Little Thing<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(69)">Goblin Domain</a><br>
<br>
total 36<br>
<br>
<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Now i know your all going to laugh at this deck and tell me certain cards are useless, or ill never pull it off.  I would just like to tell you ahead of time your wrong, make the deck, play test and you will see the powerfull beast i have created.<br>
<br>
After saying that, i would also like to add that this deck is 99.9 percent based around the deck players, play skills.  This deck doesnt play itself it needs someone who know what going on behind the wheel.<br>
<br>
Now i would like to just go over some cards, you may think shouldn&#39;t be in here.<br>
<br>
Free peoples<br>
<br>
The ruling ring: This is a matter or prefrance, with a low sized fellowship like this deck has maybe i should be using the other ring, but when it comes down to it arwens game text (discard 3 to prevent wound to frodo) is like buttah, making the common better in my mind than the rare ring. Also i have a foil ruling ring that plays in a little<br>
<br>
Arwen Elven Rider: Basicaly all you need to do is look above to the ruling ring to see why i have her.  She is also a rangers, she can cycle my hand, and gosh darnit is hot!<br>
<br>
Sam Faithful Companion: Bill the pony makes him invisible, combined with a talent and a no strangers, my fellowship moves for free, he is also there for the a promise.<br>
<br>
Midgewater Moors: This site believe it or not, in this deck mess people up.  I  normally lay down around 3 badies at site 2, making the freepeoples play make some hard choices. This site doesnt effect me much, as when i move there, there isnt much pool and i love card cycling anyhow.<br>
<br>
Bilbo Baggins Retired Adventurer: Dur if i draw the second bill i can drop it with no worries, also he bring back A Promise and a talent, and not to mention my hobbit allies, just incase something bad happens (and yes i know he cant bring back dead allies only discarded ones)<br>
<br>
Three Monstrous Trolls: Your right this is a bad card, in most decks, but not this one. First off its free and you dont have to spot anyone, so if even if it has no use its not going to clogg your hand, and you dont have to waist a discard on it, you can just play it.  But now lets think deep about this card, it makes runners  a waist of pool, and that nasty new nazgul card all but pointless, not to mention other twilight adding cards.<br>
<br>
Stone Trolls: This is really up to you, most if not all the deck in my area use uruk-hai making this card playable, and pretty good. If they dont use uruk-hai (or the cave troll) Discard it, no big deal.<br>
<br>
Shadow<br>
<br>
Now i know the first card your going to tell me to take out of my deck is.<br>
<br>
Such a little thing:  This card is kinda like stone trolls, borimir is always people his ugly little head up no matter where i go, this card ends him, and even if they have 2 possensions normally armour and a blade, or blade and a bow (on gorn) a 0 costing card that gets rid of a companion or 2 possensions is great.  There are also a good deal of decks who need Borimir to stay alive, now if they lose him turn 2 the game is all but over.  Bottom line its really up to the player.<br>
<br>
Goblin Domain: I really shouldnt have to explain this card, but i have feeling someones going to ask so here it is.  If the person i play is playing with a small fellowship there going to die to my shadow, there really isnt much of a question about it. Now a large fellowship is a bit more tricky someone playing 9 walkers or whatever there un orginal hiney is deciding play goblin domain makes those companions played after site 4, 1 shot away from death it also turns there extra compainons into a big waist of pool.<br>
<br>
Unfamiliar Territory: Who doesnt have at least one free people archer in there deck (besides me)? If it isnt legolas, or a bowed out arwen or lorien elf, its a bowed out gorn.  I cant count the number of times ive overwhelmed legolas or arwen with this card, and if they dont have archers, its still a plus 2 to str and for 0 thats not to bad, you can always play them seeing as there free again not going to clogg your hand.<br>
<br>
Tower Assassin: Some people get greedy with there elrond and draw 3 cards right away, some people like to rumil, i could go on forever with this minions uses but we all get the point.<br>
<br>
Orc Overseer: This guy made minion archery NASTY with a capitial NASTY. I am only running one to see how it goese, so far so good thinking about 2 but i can see that as a potential hand clogger. With a str of 10 he isnt going to lose a skirmish very often, normally he draws 2 shots from legolas or aragorn and that rules, because thats 4 less wounds my archers have to give.<br>
<br>
There is my deck, i took alot of time on it and i hope you judge me to harshly, keep in mind as i said befor this deck is all about play skills, if you dont have them dont bother with this deck. Also this deck was built to my style of play, mine and your style may be different keep that mind.<br>
<br>
<br>
One other thing to keep in mind while playing this deck is to not keep cards in your hand, dont save up for 4 unfamilar territories, doing stuff like that messes with this deck massive mojo.<br>
<br>
